    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "A *tattletale orb* is a polished crystal sphere that appears to function as a *crystal ball*. If those whom you use the orb to scry on roll better than a critical failure on their saving throw, they receive a telepathic message alerting them to the scrying. A success or better at the save allows the target to choose to allow you to scry anyway, knowing they can use an aspect of the orb against you, according to the orb's type. A creature that rolls a critical success on the saving throw also learns your name and location. Once you Activate a *tattletale orb* or use it to cast one of your scrying spells, it fuses to you. You must succeed at a Will save, using the scrying Will DC of a *crystal ball* of the orb's type, to use another such device.  \n  \n *Tattletale orbs* come in the same types as *crystal balls*, with the same activations and powers. However, your target must roll a critical failure on the saving throw for the orb to function as normal for that type of *crystal ball*.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 137,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "rare"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Rare",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 274,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "93177649f9920e9a2a4a80ada85b7ab1",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Cursed",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 306",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 306",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 306,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An item with this trait is cursed to cause trouble for its owner. A curse isn\u2019t detected when the item is identified, though a critical success reveals both the presence and exact nature of the curse. Cursed items can\u2019t be discarded once they\u2019ve been triggered or invested the first time. The item can be removed only if the curse is removed.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 141,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "985f7af5ffe2d17740eff2a722a117c1",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Scrying",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 460,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A scrying effect lets you see, hear, or otherwise get sensory information from a distance using a sensor or apparatus, rather than your own eyes and ears.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
